        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.9111 RR/3–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-14">March 14,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received March 14—5:22 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>870. <hi rend="italic">China Press</hi> March 14 carried Sun Fo statement on
                    arrival Shanghai from Nanking last Saturday<note n="2" xml:id="d213fn2">March
                        12.</note> that China should take neutral stand in event of third world war
                    and be neither anti-US nor anti-USSR. Sun predicted Communists would join Soviet
                    bloc when in control China. Also declared that China’s failure obtain
                    satisfactory results from past foreign policy due to deterioration in relations
                    among wartime allies which affected Chinese situation. According to Sun, China
                    was not responsible for this state of affairs, and there had been “no big
                    mistakes in China’s foreign policy”.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking 516, Canton 155.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
